00307063741/https://www.newsit.gr/ellada/koronoios-14-akoma-krousmata-stin-ellad/2988717/ |archive-date=7 March 2020 }}</ref> Health and state authorities issued precautionary guidelines and recommendations, while measures up to that point were taken locally and included the closure of schools and the suspension of cultural events in the affected areas (particularly [[Elis (regional unit)|Ilia]], [[Achaea]] and [[Zakynthos]]).<ref name=\":0\" /> The first confirmed death from COVID-19 in Greece was a 66-year-old man, who died on 12 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/greece-reports-first-coronavirus-death-66-year-old-man/ |title=Greece reports first coronavirus death, 66-year-old man |date=12 March 2020 |website=straitstimes.com |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314014704/https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/greece-reports-first-coronavirus-death-66-year-old-man |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBy 7 April, there were 1832 confirmed cases in Greece, 81 deaths and 279 recoveries.<ref name=\"greeceapril7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.onmed.gr/ygeia-eidhseis/story/383242/koronoios-nea-krousmata-simera|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 81 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 - 77 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 - 1.832 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf \u03c3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03bf|last=|first=|date=2020-04-07|website=Onmed.gr|language=el|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> The Greek [[National Public Health Organization (Greece)|National Public Health Organization]] (NPHO), in collaboration with local authorities and doctors, is tracking and testing everyone who came in close contact with the patients.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.onmed.gr/ygeia-eidhseis/story/382322/koronoios-stin-patra-to-enato-kroysma |titl