reary \u2013 Human Target Soundtrack|url=http://www.seattlepi.com/lifestyle/blogcritics/article/Music-Review-Bear-McCreary-Human-Target-879348.php|work=Seattle Post-Intelligencer|accessdate=September 18, 2013|date=April 26, 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2010\u2013present\n| ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]''\n| 131 episodes\n[[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers|ASCAP Award for Top Television Series]]\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[The Cape (2011 TV series)|The Cape]]''\n| 10 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2012\n|''[[Day Break]]''\n|5 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[Holliston (TV series)|Holliston]]''\n| 17 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[Battlestar Galactica: Blood and Chrome]]''\n| 10 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n|''[[Metalocalypse: The Doomstar Requiem]]''\n|[[Television film]]<br>Composed with [[Brendon Small]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2013\u20132015\n|''[[Defiance (TV series)|Defiance]]''\n| 38 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[Da Vinci's Demons]]''\n| 28 episodes\n[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Original Main Title Theme Music]]<ref>{{cite web| url= https://variety.com/2013/tv/news/emmys-creative-arts-emmys-live-blog-1200612516/ |work= Variety| date= September 15, 2013 |title= LIVE From the Creative Arts Emmys: Tracking the winners at Sunday's Creative Arts ceremony| first= Jon| last= Weisman| access-date= December 6, 2017}}</ref><br>Nominated- [[International Film Music Critics Association|IFMCA Award for Best Original Score for a Television Series]]\n|-\n| 2013\u2013present\n|''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]''\n| 106 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2014\n|''[[Intruders (TV series)|Intruders]]''\n| 8 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[Constantine (TV series)|Constantine]]''\n| 13 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\u201317\n|''[[Black Sails (TV series)|Black Sails]]''\n| 38 episodes\nNominated- [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Original Main Title Theme Music]]<br>Nominated- [[International Film Music Critics Association|IFMCA Award for Best Original Score for a Television Series]]\n|-\n| 2014\u201319\n|''[[Outl